            "summary": "Booz Allen Hamilton Holding Corporation, listed on NYSE as BAH, is set to reveal its fourth-quarter earnings on May 23. Analysts' predictions suggest earnings of $1.61 per share, showing growth from $1.33 per share in the same quarter last year. Based in McLean, Virginia, the company is expected to announce quarterly revenue of $3.03 billion, an increase from $2.77 billion in the previous year. Recently, Booz Allen Hamilton collaborated with Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: META) to unveil \"Space Llama,\" an AI solution aimed at improving maintenance and repair operations on the International Space Station. The closing stock price for Booz Allen Hamilton was $129.13, reflecting a 0.6% increase, as of last Thursday. For further details, readers can consult the latest analyst ratings on the Analyst section of a financial platform.",
